author: News Tribune
title: Women's Volleyball: Engelbrecht stars for William Woods
text:
Share 
William Woods sophomore setter Brittney Engelbrecht compiled 65 total assists in the Lady Owls’ victories against Benedictine College (35) on Tuesday and Stephens College (30) on Wednesday. 
Engelbrecht, a Helias graduate, had seven kills in a home non-conference match against Benedictine and six at conference-foe Stephens. She also had seven and nine digs, respectively. 
William Woods (20-10, 9-1 American Midwest Conference) defeated Benedictine in four games (25-15, 25-23, 23-25, 25-20) and Stephens in three (25-21, 25-18, 25-20). 
Engelbrecht currently leads the team in assists with 1,039 and in aces with 31. The mark also puts her in fourth in the AMC. 
Engelbrecht’s average of 10.29 assists per game places her 18th in NAIA Division I. ﻿
